@jowrotethis All of that only works for me if  it leads to the return of *that* Luke. And we never really get it. Even at the end, I thought, "Luke's back!" And then he flapped into the breeze. His relationship with Rey and his cowardly retreat are never really resolved.

@jowrotethis And for the most part, I think TLJ did a great job with the hand it was dealt. I still don't buy that the Luke Skywalker we knew would just leave Ben to rise to power with the Dark Side, but Johnson took him to interesting places. That said...
